description:
Bug 38131ajc needs -d option. I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have to do with a change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

To reproduce:
1. Create a class in a subpackage, such as:

package subpackage;

public class Test {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Hello");
    }
}

2. Compile using the following command:

ajc -d subpackage\ Test.java

You will see a directory "subpackage" created under the existing "subpackage" directory. subpackage\Test.java or javac subpackage\Test.java.

No big deal, really.
